    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"collapse\" is one of the biggest mysteries in quantum mechanics, and it's where the debate is fiercest among physicists. Some theories, like the Many-Worlds Interpretation, suggest the wave function doesn't truly collapse but rather the universe splits into branches reflecting every possible outcome. Other interpretations, like objective collapse theories, propose that a real physical mechanism forces the system into a definite state when observed. Currently, there is no single, universally accepted theory that fully explains *what* the collapse mechanism truly is.",
